        <div class="content2">
            <h2>The Harsh Reality</h2>
            <p>
                Feasting in Abundance, Ignoring the Hunger Crisis
                In the heart of our vibrant nation, India, where festivals are celebrated with grandeur and weddings
                are
                extravagant affairs, there lies a stark contrast. While some indulge in lavish banquets, countless
                others
                struggle to put food on their plates. It's disheartening to witness the sheer amount of food that
                goes to
                waste at events and restaurants, especially when millions are left hungry and malnourished.
            </p>

        </div>


    </div>
    <br><br>
    <div class="para2">
        <div class="content2">
            <h2>One Man's Feast, Another's Famine</h2>
            <p>
                Food wastage is a critical issue that not only depletes our precious resources but also widens the
                gap
                between the privileged and the underprivileged. We've all seen it – the untouched, uneaten meals
                left to
                perish while a few kilometers away, families are grappling with hunger.
            </p>

        </div>
        <img src="assets/img2.jpg" id="para2" alt="para2">


    </div>
    <br><br>
    <div class="para2">
        <img src="assets/img3.jpeg" id="para2" alt="para2">
        <div class="content2">
            <h2>Our Vision: A Simple Solution with Profound Impact</h2>
            <p>
                At SHARE AND SUSTAIN, we envision a world where no one sleeps on an empty stomach, where surplus
                food
                becomes a lifeline for those in need. Our mission is clear – to create a platform that connects
                restaurants,
                marriage halls, and event venues with NGOs, ensuring that excess food is rescued and redirected to
                those who
                need it the most.
            </p>

        </div>
    </div><br><br>
    <div class="container">
        <h2>How We Make a Difference</h2>
        <div class="flex">
            <div class="div1">
                <h3>Restaurants and Venues: Partners in Change</h3>
                <p>
                    Join hands with us as we encourage restaurants, marriage halls, and event venues to become
                    partners in
                    change. By simply notifying us about the surplus food after an event, these establishments
                    become beacons of
                    hope for the less fortunate.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="div2">
                <h3>NGOs: The Backbone of Our Mission</h3>
                <p>
                    Our network of NGOs plays a pivotal role in ensuring that rescued food reaches those in need
                    promptly and
                    safely. These organizations are the unsung heroes, making a real difference in the lives of the
                    hungry and
                    the marginalized.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <br><br>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="flex">
            <div class="div1">
                <h3>Get Involved, Make an Impact</h3>
                <p>
                    You have the power to make a difference. Join us in our mission to turn surplus into sustenance.
                    Whether you
                    are a restaurant owner, a concerned citizen, or a potential volunteer, your contribution matters.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="div2">
                <h3>Together, We Can End Hunger</h3>
                <p>
